    "body": "Set index does not sort the data as it is setting. You maybe need to do this.\n\nSee here: http://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/dev/indexing.html#the-need-for-sortedness-with-multiindex\n\nTheir are performance reasons for having the user sorting (rather than automatic sorting).\n\n```\nIn [8]: stacked.sortlevel()\nOut[8]: \n                     Value\nID Count Value_type       \nx  1     bar             3\n         foo             1\n   2     foo             2\ny  1     bar             5\n         baz             6\n         foo             4\n\n[6 rows x 1 columns]\n```\n"
